# Platform Architecture Rules

## Intent
Define the structural rules for the rewrite product so mini-app messaging and command systems remain modular, safe, and maintainable.

## Mandatory
- Treat mini-app experience surfaces as the core product model; capabilities are invoked as mini-app commands/actions.
- Keep mini-app command execution behind a centralized policy and permission layer.
- Use shared contracts for web/mobile/backend payloads and command schemas.
- Isolate mini-app domains to avoid cross-domain coupling and unintended data sharing.
- Enforce explicit ownership for each bounded context and mini-app.
- Use mini-app-scoped feature naming (for example, `chyme-chat`) instead of ambiguous global names like `chat`.

## Integration Rules
- No mini-app command path may bypass core messaging policy middleware.
- No mini-app may access another mini-app's sensitive storage without an approved shared contract.
- Introduce adapters at boundaries when integrating legacy concepts.

## Release Blockers
- New mini-app capability path that is not represented as a mini-app command contract.
- Feature architecture that bypasses centralized auth, policy, or audit hooks.